South African 28th seed Kevin Anderson defeated 17th-seeded American Sam Querrey 7-6 (7/5), 6-7 (9/11), 6-3, 7-6 (9/7) to reach the US Open semi-finals on Tuesday.Anderson, the US Open s first South African semi-finalist since Cliff Drysdale in 1965, will meet Spanish 12th seed Pablo Carreno Busta on Friday for a place in Sunday s final.